49966f6927a5f7bd7f6ea12ffe7fe5073fd9fc72.body:
Origin: https://github.com/webmproject/libvpx/commit/6a7c84a2449dcc70de2525df209afea908622399
Author: James Zern <jzern@google.com>

-----
This is a security fix for CVE-2019-2126. Godot currently contains a vulnerable
version of libwebm in its 3.x branch that is susceptible to a double free due
to a missing reset of a freed pointer. This commit corrects that issue.

c8317fc926d6e8c5f87fef59cb4738489cc69c06.summary: `Object::call()` prevent debug lock accessing dangling pointer
c8317fc926d6e8c5f87fef59cb4738489cc69c06.body:
Self deleting an object within a call was leading to crashes due to referencing freed memory, due to a raw pointer stored in the debug lock.

Co-authored-by: RandomShaper <pedrojrulez@gmail.com>
(cherry picked from commit 0ccd559d176b5e0d0c72128c382b6cad525438c2)

5b8b9adb353b2c8c70e1ecc334c7c9c0b41e9e1e.body:
Lifetime checks for stored `RIDs` for collision objects assumed they had valid `object_ids`.
It turns out that some are not derived from `Object` and thus checking `ObjectDB` returns false for some valid `RIDs`.
To account for this we only perform lifetime checks on valid `object_ids`.

(cherry picked from commit d4cca62bb47feabbc2306379f57a1f52b82d738b)
